teoreetilise ja praktilise teabe, mis on vajalik iseseisvaks tööks üldarstina. Teoreetilisi teadmisi õpitakse õpikute ning Moodle'i e-kursusel olevate konspektide, videoloengute ja enesetestide abil. Mikroskoopiliste muutuste õppimine toimub digitaalsete histopreparaatide alusel, mis on kättesaadavad e-kursusel koos õppevideotega teemade kaupa grupeeritud andmebaasidena. Seminarides toimub iseseisvalt omandatud teabe kinnistamine ja seostamine kliiniliste haigusjuhtudega. </p>The course provides theoretical and practical knowledge about pathological diagnostics of surgical, oncological and other gynecological, breast and skin diseases, required for independent work as a general practitioner. The sources of theoretical knowledge are the textbooks and presentations, video lectures and self-assessment tests represented in the Moodle learning platform. For learning of microscopic alterations, the database of digital microscopy slides with tutorial videos is available in the Moodle, grouped according to the topics. In the seminars, discussions of independently learned materials takes place and drawing associations with clinical significance.</div>
